  "commentary": "**Dealer Hedging Commentary:**\n\nWith SPX at 6550.82 in PIN regime, dealers are positioned below the 6578 flip level and well under the massive 11.35B positive gamma wall at 6580, creating strong upside resistance as dealers will aggressively sell any rally toward that strike. The current positioning suggests dealers are providing natural support around current levels while capping upside moves, with mean reversion behavior expected to keep price rangebound between the 6500 negative gamma amplifier floor and 6580 ceiling. Watch for increased volatility if we break below 6500 where dealers flip to buying (amplifying downside) or sustained buying pressure needed to clear the 6565-6580 gamma wall cluster above.",
